<subSubSection id="C5FC6527E553FFC5369AFEEFCEA4FDD9" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D5936ACE553FFC5369AFEEFCE76FEF8" blockId="10.[189,310,267,293]" box="[189,310,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading id="D61181C0E553FFC5369AFEEFCE76FEF8" bold="true" box="[189,310,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="3">
<emphasis id="BF92EABEE553FFC5369AFEEFCE76FEF8" bold="true" box="[189,310,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D5936ACE553FFC5369AFEDDCEA4FDD9" blockId="10.[189,1398,313,516]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName id="4AE64D2FE553FFC5369AFEDDCE13FE8E" authorityName="Rafinesque-Schmaltz" authorityYear="1815" box="[189,339,313,339]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbricidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lumbricinae">Lumbricinae</taxonomicName>
of large to very large size, post-clitellar trapezoidal section. Pigmentation brown to dark brown. Prostomium epilobous, closed. Longitudinal furrows in the peristomium. Nephridial pores “en solfège” (irregularly distributed). Spermathecal pores at least in two intersegments, between 9/10 and 13/14, or 13/14 and 15/16, sometimes multiple. Anterior septa strongly thickened. Male pores in 
<emphasis id="BF92EABEE553FFC53314FE47CA0AFE60" bold="true" box="[1331,1354,419,445]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">½</emphasis>
15, usually with porophores. Gizzard in 17–20 (21, 22). Typhlosole pinnate. Two or four pairs of seminal vesicles in (9, 10) 11, 12.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
